 Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available.JOHANNESBURG - The man accused of killing 22-year-old Karabo Mokoena was denied bail in the Johannesburg Magistrate's Court on Friday.Sandile Mantsoe denied murdering his ex-girlfriend. Magistrate Labuschagne: The court is satisfied by argument presented by the State that this was murder. #SandileMantsoe Defense: If #SandileMantsoe tried to defeat the ends of justice he would have destroyed the evidence. READ: Mantsoe confessed to murdering Mokoena to sever blood-tie: NPA The 27-year-old accused claimed that Mokoena committed suicide. The state says #SandileMantsoe didn't disclose the position of the deceased body when he found her."Did she hang herself, did she overdose?" But the state maintained Mantsoe had murdered Mokoena in a ritual killing in order to sever the blood tie between them, and restore his failing business.Prosecutors said it was unclear whether Mokoena was alive when her body was doused with petrol and set alight.The case was postponed to July 28.eNCA